"{\"uid\": \"independent.co.uk-voices-letters-simone-biles-olympics-tory-leadership-labour-b2587295.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Notifications can be managed in browser preferences.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in  Swipe for next article  Lettersto the editor: our readers share their views.\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 268, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please send your letters to letters@independent.co.uk  It was heartening to see Olympic gymnast Simone Biles make her return to this year's games after being thrown off at the Tokyo Olympicsdue to a case of the \\\"twisties\\\".\", \"from\": 269, \"to\": 491, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 365, \"end\": 377, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Simone Biles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite its amusing name, the twisties refers to a psychological condition similar to the \\\"yips\\\", or even writer's block, where a person who usually is proficient in a particular skill (in this case gymnastics) is suddenly unable to perform under pressure.\", \"from\": 492, \"to\": 748, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Biles hasdescribed the conditionas like being \\\"lost in the air\\\", saying \\\"your mind and your body are at a disconnect.\", \"from\": 750, \"to\": 867, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Your body is going to try to do something, and your mind is going to be like, 'No, you are not doing this'\\\".\", \"from\": 868, \"to\": 976, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite not possessing nearly the same level of skill as Biles, I have experienced my own version of the twisties many times - as, I imagine, have many people.\", \"from\": 978, \"to\": 1137, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There is nothing worse than suddenly experiencing that sensation of vertigo when doing something you have done many times before.\", \"from\": 1138, \"to\": 1267, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Luckily, must of us do not experience iton the world stage.\", \"from\": 1268, \"to\": 1327, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Returning to this year's Olympics after such an episode is an inspiration, and a reminder that no matter how hard we fall, we can always pick ourselves back up again.\", \"from\": 1329, \"to\": 1495, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Stephen Bloom  Canterbury  I was interested to read in Sunday's edition that Dame Priti Patel wouldhand back some control of policy to ordinary party membersand allow them to elect key officials.\", \"from\": 1497, \"to\": 1692, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Those are presumably the same ordinary party members who elected Liz Truss as leader and prime minister.\", \"from\": 1694, \"to\": 1798, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1759, \"end\": 1768, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liz_Truss\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Liz Truss\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liz_Truss\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liz_Truss\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What can possibly go wrong?\", \"from\": 1799, \"to\": 1826, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"John Coppendale  Cambridge  The new government is to be commended for its publicly stated objective to govern with openness and transparency.\", \"from\": 1828, \"to\": 1969, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1845, \"end\": 1854, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Cambridge\", \"score\": 0.9798886821692542, \"rank\": 0.020523997072719114, \"text\": \"Cambridge\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Cambridge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Cambridge\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is desperately needed following years of Tory deceits, obfuscation and corruption.\", \"from\": 1970, \"to\": 2057, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is crucial to restore trust in democracy and UK politics.\", \"from\": 2058, \"to\": 2118, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2106, \"end\": 2117, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Politics_of_the_United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"UK politics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Politics_of_the_United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Politics_of_the_United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Everyone - the public, our institutions, business, the media, the trade unions, so-called \\\"think tanks\\\" and pressure groups - all have their own vested interests in promoting their own version of honesty.\", \"from\": 2120, \"to\": 2324, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Most of us have an incomplete picture of, for example, the state of the economy, and few are in a position to give a balanced view.\", \"from\": 2325, \"to\": 2456, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But that will not prevent many from expressing their own version of events.\", \"from\": 2457, \"to\": 2532, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This will get personal, aggressive and feed the populist vultures.\", \"from\": 2533, \"to\": 2599, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It will be easy to ascribe ulterior motives to our new, open and transparent government.\", \"from\": 2601, \"to\": 2689, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We need to focus on the facts, and we need to cut the new government some slack.\", \"from\": 2691, \"to\": 2771, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Openness and transparency are so much more difficult than the half-truths, partial pictures and ideological bias that we have become accustomed to, and take a heavy toll on the personal honesty and integrity of its champions.\", \"from\": 2772, \"to\": 2997, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is a risky management style, but it is the right one.\", \"from\": 2998, \"to\": 3054, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Is the country ready for it, or will bitterness and cynicism continue to prevail?\", \"from\": 3056, \"to\": 3137, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"David Lowndes  Southampton  I, along with I am sure many people, am having trouble adjusting to a media cycle which does not confront us with some cringeworthy government embarrassment or outrage every 48 hours.\", \"from\": 3139, \"to\": 3350, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Labour are by no means perfect, but it cannot be denied that they are much better at keeping their heads down and getting on with the job - so far, at least.\", \"from\": 3352, \"to\": 3509, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Let us just hope that it lasts.\", \"from\": 3511, \"to\": 3542, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Molly Howe  Liverpool  Join thought-provoking conversations, follow other Independent readers and see their replies  Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in\", \"from\": 3544, \"to\": 3797, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3544, \"end\": 3549, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Molly_Hayes\", \"score\": 0.9999628759721314, \"rank\": 2.870551650301835e-05, \"text\": \"Molly\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Molly_Hayes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Molly_Hayes\"}, {\"begin\": 3556, \"end\": 3565, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liverpool_F.C.\", \"score\": 0.8271059889845337, \"rank\": 0.2090325991461282, \"text\": \"Liverpool\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liverpool_F.C.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liverpool_F.C.\"}, {\"begin\": 3618, \"end\": 3629, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.472283968575544e-27, \"text\": \"Independent\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\"}]}]}"